y, extending significantly the scope of current scholarship. Essays scrutinise the author’s prolonged concern with domestic, communal and national violence, his interrogation of patterns of inheritance and ideological heritage, and the impact of the past on choices his characters make. William Trevor: Revaluations is a groundbreaking collection of essays, and will also be seen as a definitive introduction to the work of a major contemporary novelist and short-story writer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aAristotle.  aEngland.  aEnglish language.  aWilliam Trevor.  aacts of cruelty.  abetrayals.  adancehall days.  aemotional turbulence.  aethics.  afamily memories.  aliberal humanist premises.  amigrant themes.  anostalgia.  ascreen fictions.  avision of tragedy.1 aDelaney, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelaney, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHand, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansson, Heidi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerron, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInnes, C.L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJeffers, Jennifer M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy-Andrews, Elmer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Hermione, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Brien, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neill, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Toole, Tina, 